CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778803375
OL,3,CBurnham eyes Westminster return as MP
OL,4,Cstands aside to allow challenge to
OL,5,CStarmer
OL,7,FHe said: "We owe it to people to come
OL,8,Fback together as a Labour movement,
OL,9,Fgiving the Prime Minister and the
OL,10,FGovernment the space and stability
OL,11,Fthey need as the by-election takes
OL,12,Fplace."
OL,14,FThat announcement came within minutes
OL,15,Fof Mr Simons, a former Starmer
OL,16,Floyalist who quit as a minister in
OL,17,FFebruary amid controversy over a think
OL,18,Ftank he used to run, calling for a
OL,19,F"change in leadership" as he announced
OL,20,Fhe would stand down as an MP for Mr
OL,21,FBurnham.
OL,26,@oD@JOUtD@GO]{D@AOU{D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
